\chapter{Simulation of Lennard-Jones samples}

The phenomenology observed in experiments on glass formers can be understood with the aid of simple models.   

Binary mixtures of particles interacting via an isotropic Lennard-Jones potential of the form 
\begin{equation}
	\phi_{ij}(r) = 4\epsilon_{ij} \left[ \left( \frac{\sigma_{ij}}{r} \right)^{12} - \left( \frac{\sigma_{ij}}{r} \right)^{6} \right] 
\end{equation}

has been extensively used in numerical and simulation work to probe and reproduce the behaviour of glassy systems. \todo[inline]{la roba numerica Ã¨ MCT}

